    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I see. So basically, I could end up paying for their mistakes if the wording is bad. Are there specific \"red flag\" words I should look out for in these types of clauses that might indicate I'm being taken advantage of?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yes, you're right to be wary of overly broad language; it's a common trap. Look out for phrases like \"any and all claims,\" \"sole negligence,\" or language that makes you indemnify them for their own gross negligence or willful misconduct. If the clause doesn't clearly limit the scope of what you are responsible for, it's a massive red flag. These words can be interpreted by a court to mean you cover everything, even things outside your control.",
      "source": "target",
